question.title: Codename One Plugin not loading with IntelliJ
question.body:
I have an IntelliJ IDE on a Windows 11 installation running. The cn1 GIT repositories are connected. I installed the IntelliJ IDE in C:\eclipse\IntelliJ. answers.body:
It seems that the build is being executed with a JRE instead of a JDK. Check the JVM used for the project.

Could not find artifact com.sun:tools:jar:1.8.0 at specified path C:\eclipse\Java_JRE_8/../lib/tools.jar

79675457.body: That is correct, but I also doubt it will work once that is fixed. Codename One doesn't support the inclusion of arbitrary jars into the top level project since they might rely on functionality that isn't available in the native platform. This can be added to the Android sub project but for the iOS subproject OP would need to use the iOS native braintree support.
